# Vito Store Landing Page Prototype

This plan outlines the steps and architecture for creating a high-conversion Next.js landing page for Vito Store, based on the Instagram analysis.

## Proposed Changes

### Setup Envrionment
- Initialize a new Next.js project in `c:\Users\Usuario\VitoStoreWeb`.
- Use the App Router and TypeScript.
- **Styling:** Use standard CSS Modules (since the use of Tailwind is restricted unless requested).

### Components Structure
- **[NEW] `src/app/page.tsx`:** The main landing page joining all sections.
- **[NEW] `src/app/globals.css`:** Global styles applying the color palette:
  - Background: White (`#FFFFFF`)
  - Accents: Purple (`#6A0DAD`) / Pink (`#FFC0CB`)
  - Highlights: Red (`#E50914`) for product elements.
- **[NEW] `src/components/Header.tsx`:** Sticky navigation bar with the Vito Store logo.
- **[NEW] `src/components/HeroSection.tsx`:** High-impact "Above the fold" section with a catchy phrase ("Lencería que te abraza en Corrientes") and a call to action.
- **[NEW] `src/components/CatalogoSection.tsx`:** A grid displaying three distinct categories: `Lencería`, `Trajes de Baño`, and `Pijamas`.
- **[NEW] `src/components/MayoristaSection.tsx`:** A dedicated block for resellers with a clear Call to Action leading to WhatsApp.
- **[NEW] `src/components/SocialProofSection.tsx`:** The `Team Vitö` dynamic carousel showing customer reviews/photos.
- **[NEW] `src/components/FloatingWhatsApp.tsx`:** A persistent floating button for quick contact.

### Backend Integrations (Mocked)
- **[NEW] `src/services/sheets.ts`:** A placeholder function demonstrating how to fetch prices or catalog data from a Google Sheet in the future.

## Verification Plan

### Automated Tests
* The setup will be verified by running `npm run build` and ensuring there are no TypeScript or Next.js build errors.

### Manual Verification
* Execute `npm run dev` to start the local Next.js server.
* Capture a visual screenshot of the Header and Hero section to validate the design against the requested palette and high-conversion structure.
